WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.565
Welcome to our guide on the civil commitment

2
00:00:02.565 --> 00:00:03.645
process in Utah.

3
00:00:04.355 --> 00:00:06.645
This process is designed to help individuals

4
00:00:06.645 --> 00:00:09.405
with severe mental illness receive the care they need,

5
00:00:09.715 --> 00:00:11.525
even when they may not be able to make

6
00:00:11.525 --> 00:00:12.565
that decision on their own.

7
00:00:13.615 --> 00:00:16.205
Civil commitment is a legal process for individuals

8
00:00:16.205 --> 00:00:18.805
with severe mental illness who require a court order

9
00:00:18.825 --> 00:00:20.685
for mental health treatment in a hospital

10
00:00:20.785 --> 00:00:21.885
or outpatient clinic.

11
00:00:22.705 --> 00:00:26.205
The goal is to ensure their safety and the safety of others.

12
00:00:27.105 --> 00:00:30.125
In Utah, there are five criteria that must be met

13
00:00:30.145 --> 00:00:32.645
for an adult to be involuntarily committed.

14
00:00:33.375 --> 00:00:35.125
First, the person has a mental illness

15
00:00:35.125 --> 00:00:37.485
that substantially impairs their behavioral

16
00:00:37.985 --> 00:00:39.325
or emotional functioning.

17
00:00:39.985 --> 00:00:43.125
Second, the individual presents a substantial danger

18
00:00:43.265 --> 00:00:44.525
to themselves or others.

19
00:00:45.455 --> 00:00:47.885
Third, the individual is not capable

20
00:00:48.145 --> 00:00:49.925
of making rational decisions.

21
00:00:50.585 --> 00:00:54.085
Fourth, there is no less restrictive alternative available.

22
00:00:54.975 --> 00:00:58.085
Fifth, the treatment is adequate and appropriate.

23
00:00:59.115 --> 00:01:02.245
It's important to note that all five criteria must be met

24
00:01:02.245 --> 00:01:04.645
for an adult to be involuntarily committed.

25
00:01:05.345 --> 00:01:08.205
How do you know an individual presents a substantial danger

26
00:01:08.345 --> 00:01:09.525
to themselves or others?

27
00:01:09.955 --> 00:01:12.565
Substantial dangers means that due to mental illness,

28
00:01:12.785 --> 00:01:16.405
an individual is at serious risk of suicide,

29
00:01:16.675 --> 00:01:19.685
serious bodily injury because of their actions

30
00:01:19.705 --> 00:01:22.365
or inaction, suffer serious bodily injury

31
00:01:22.365 --> 00:01:25.405
because they're incapable of providing the basic necessities

32
00:01:25.405 --> 00:01:28.845
of life, such as food, clothing, and shelter, causing

33
00:01:28.945 --> 00:01:31.525
or attempting to cause serious bodily injury,

34
00:01:32.525 --> 00:01:34.485
engaging in harmful sexual conduct.

35
00:01:35.525 --> 00:01:37.845
Additionally, substantial danger means that if not treated,

36
00:01:38.075 --> 00:01:40.965
suffering, severe and abnormal mental, emotional,

37
00:01:41.105 --> 00:01:43.045
or physical distress that is associated

38
00:01:43.045 --> 00:01:46.125
with significant impairment in judgment, reason or behavior,

39
00:01:46.425 --> 00:01:49.085
and causes a substantial deterioration in the individual's

40
00:01:49.285 --> 00:01:50.965
previous ability to function independently.

41
00:01:51.435 --> 00:01:54.325
Most mental health services are provided voluntarily.

42
00:01:54.835 --> 00:01:58.005
However, if someone is in crisis and a danger to themselves

43
00:01:58.065 --> 00:01:59.965
or others and unable to make decisions

44
00:01:59.965 --> 00:02:01.845
regarding their treatment emergency,

45
00:02:02.125 --> 00:02:03.565
temporary commitment may be necessary.

46
00:02:04.035 --> 00:02:06.965
This can happen through either a pink sheet or a blue sheet.

47
00:02:07.315 --> 00:02:10.325
Both the pink sheet and a blue sheet hold a patient for up

48
00:02:10.325 --> 00:02:13.445
to 72 hours, excluding holidays and weekends.

49
00:02:13.755 --> 00:02:16.125
They get a person from the community to the ER

50
00:02:16.125 --> 00:02:17.285
for further evaluation.

51
00:02:17.905 --> 00:02:18.965
It is important to note

52
00:02:18.965 --> 00:02:21.525
that there is no minimum time required for a hold

53
00:02:21.545 --> 00:02:23.085
and it does not guarantee admission

54
00:02:23.145 --> 00:02:24.405
to an inpatient facility.

55
00:02:25.015 --> 00:02:26.365
While functionally pink

56
00:02:26.385 --> 00:02:29.205
and blue sheets are the same, there are differences.

57
00:02:30.035 --> 00:02:32.325
Pink sheets or emergency applications

58
00:02:32.345 --> 00:02:35.365
for involuntary commitment without certification can be

59
00:02:35.365 --> 00:02:37.645
signed by law enforcement or peace officers

60
00:02:37.665 --> 00:02:38.845
or mental health officers.

61
00:02:39.435 --> 00:02:41.565
They must observe the conduct that leads them

62
00:02:41.565 --> 00:02:44.445
to believe an individual poses a substantial danger

63
00:02:44.505 --> 00:02:45.765
to themselves or others.

64
00:02:46.925 --> 00:02:49.645
A mental health officer is an individual designated

65
00:02:49.665 --> 00:02:52.605
by a local mental health authority is qualified by training

66
00:02:52.665 --> 00:02:54.325
and experience in the recognition

67
00:02:54.325 --> 00:02:56.045
and identification of mental illness.

68
00:02:56.615 --> 00:02:59.805
After a pink sheet is signed, then the patient needs to go

69
00:02:59.805 --> 00:03:01.525
to the ER for another evaluation.

70
00:03:02.065 --> 00:03:05.165
If they're going involuntarily, they'll be transported

71
00:03:05.165 --> 00:03:06.445
by EMS or police.

72
00:03:07.155 --> 00:03:09.325
Blue sheets or emergency application

73
00:03:09.345 --> 00:03:12.405
for involuntary commitment with certification must be signed

74
00:03:12.405 --> 00:03:13.685
by two different individuals.

75
00:03:14.145 --> 00:03:17.485
The front side is signed by an Ian, who is anyone

76
00:03:17.645 --> 00:03:19.285
with knowledge of the person's behavior.

77
00:03:20.155 --> 00:03:22.245
They have observed the individual's conduct

78
00:03:22.545 --> 00:03:23.805
and have firsthand knowledge

79
00:03:23.805 --> 00:03:26.725
of the facts indicating mental illness and risk of injury.

80
00:03:27.435 --> 00:03:30.685
This can include a family member, emergency room nurse,

81
00:03:30.745 --> 00:03:31.765
or crisis worker.

82
00:03:32.625 --> 00:03:34.805
The backside is signed by a medical doctor,

83
00:03:34.915 --> 00:03:37.725
physician's assistant, licensed nurse practitioner,

84
00:03:38.185 --> 00:03:39.725
or a designated examiner.

85
00:03:46.175 --> 00:03:49.365
After the temporary whole three outcomes are possible.

86
00:03:50.025 --> 00:03:51.565
One, if the patient has improved

87
00:03:51.585 --> 00:03:53.685
and no longer meets civil commitment criteria,

88
00:03:54.065 --> 00:03:55.725
the patient can be discharged home

89
00:03:55.905 --> 00:03:57.205
or to another level of care.

90
00:03:57.745 --> 00:04:00.605
Two. If the patient continues to meet civil criteria

91
00:04:00.705 --> 00:04:02.645
for commitment, then you can move forward

92
00:04:02.645 --> 00:04:04.845
with an application for involuntary commitment,

93
00:04:04.845 --> 00:04:06.365
otherwise known as a white sheet.

94
00:04:06.735 --> 00:04:09.125
Three. The patient becomes voluntary.

95
00:04:09.705 --> 00:04:11.685
The patient understands the need for treatment

96
00:04:12.145 --> 00:04:15.125
and is willing to stay in a hospital to get that treatment.

97
00:04:17.015 --> 00:04:18.635
If the patient becomes voluntary

98
00:04:18.895 --> 00:04:20.635
and then changes their mind at any point

99
00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:22.955
during the hospital stay, they do have the right

100
00:04:22.955 --> 00:04:25.155
to request release from an inpatient facility.

101
00:04:25.705 --> 00:04:28.515
They would do this by completing a request for release form.

102
00:04:29.015 --> 00:04:31.435
If the treatment team does not feel the patient is stable

103
00:04:31.435 --> 00:04:33.555
for discharge, they will respond

104
00:04:33.555 --> 00:04:35.315
with a denial of release form.

105
00:04:35.855 --> 00:04:38.835
The denial holds the patient for up to 48 hours.

106
00:04:39.365 --> 00:04:41.915
After 48 hours, the patient will be discharged

107
00:04:42.175 --> 00:04:44.435
and can resume treatment as a voluntary patient

108
00:04:44.935 --> 00:04:46.115
or if they need to be held longer.

109
00:04:46.255 --> 00:04:47.995
An application for involuntary hold,

110
00:04:48.095 --> 00:04:49.875
the white sheet would need to be filled out.

111
00:04:50.255 --> 00:04:52.275
The white sheet or application for order

112
00:04:52.275 --> 00:04:54.235
of involuntary commitment is signed

113
00:04:54.235 --> 00:04:56.235
by an defiant on the front and an MD

114
00:04:56.335 --> 00:04:58.035
or designated examiner on the back.

115
00:04:58.455 --> 00:05:00.915
It must include specific information as to

116
00:05:00.915 --> 00:05:03.555
how the patient meets the criteria for civil commitment.

117
00:05:03.815 --> 00:05:05.315
The application needs to be filled

118
00:05:05.335 --> 00:05:06.675
and signed, then sent

119
00:05:06.675 --> 00:05:08.555
to the appropriate district court in your area.

120
00:05:08.985 --> 00:05:10.875
Once you have submitted the white sheet

121
00:05:10.875 --> 00:05:12.395
to the appropriate district court,

122
00:05:12.595 --> 00:05:15.155
a hearing date will be set before the hearing.

123
00:05:15.375 --> 00:05:16.635
The patient will be interviewed

124
00:05:16.635 --> 00:05:18.795
by two independent designated examiners

125
00:05:19.135 --> 00:05:20.915
who will review the patient's medical records.

126
00:05:21.495 --> 00:05:23.235
The patient will also be assigned an

127
00:05:23.435 --> 00:05:24.795
attorney at the hearing.

128
00:05:25.335 --> 00:05:26.875
The judge will determine whether

129
00:05:26.975 --> 00:05:29.235
or not to impose an order of commitment.

130
00:05:29.535 --> 00:05:32.275
If the judge decides the commitment criteria are not met,

131
00:05:32.275 --> 00:05:33.355
they can dismiss the case

132
00:05:33.575 --> 00:05:35.635
and the patient will be able to leave the hospital

133
00:05:35.855 --> 00:05:37.075
and return to the community.

134
00:05:42.525 --> 00:05:44.795
Commitment orders are typically placed for 30,

135
00:05:45.085 --> 00:05:46.675
60, or 90 days.

136
00:05:47.385 --> 00:05:50.275
They do not exceed six months at the end

137
00:05:50.275 --> 00:05:51.395
of the order's timeframe.

138
00:05:51.615 --> 00:05:54.195
The patient must return to the court for a review hearing.

139
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:57.645
If during the order's timeframe a patient improves,

140
00:05:57.905 --> 00:06:00.325
the involuntary hold may not need to continue.

141
00:06:00.945 --> 00:06:02.325
If this is the case, a notice

142
00:06:02.385 --> 00:06:05.125
to drop commitment proceedings form should be completed

143
00:06:05.125 --> 00:06:06.245
before the review hearing

144
00:06:06.345 --> 00:06:08.085
and filed with the local district court.

145
00:06:08.635 --> 00:06:11.325
Once you've sent the notice of drop to the district courts,

146
00:06:11.425 --> 00:06:13.165
the court is no longer involved in treatment.

147
00:06:13.705 --> 00:06:15.125
The patient has improved enough.

148
00:06:15.145 --> 00:06:17.965
You no longer think they need to be on an involuntary hold.

149
00:06:18.425 --> 00:06:20.365
You can have them sign as a voluntary patient

150
00:06:20.505 --> 00:06:22.685
and continue in the hospital receiving treatment,

151
00:06:23.025 --> 00:06:25.085
or if they've improved enough as determined

152
00:06:25.085 --> 00:06:27.125
by the treatment team, they can be discharged

153
00:06:27.125 --> 00:06:28.525
to home or to the community.

154
00:06:28.675 --> 00:06:30.765
Alternatively, during the orders timeframe,

155
00:06:30.945 --> 00:06:33.485
the treatment team may decide the patient still needs

156
00:06:33.565 --> 00:06:36.005
treatment but hasn't improved enough to step down

157
00:06:36.005 --> 00:06:37.445
to a less restrictive setting.

158
00:06:38.025 --> 00:06:39.965
In this case, a notice of transfer

159
00:06:40.105 --> 00:06:42.605
and conditional release need to be filled out.

160
00:06:43.165 --> 00:06:45.285
A notice of transfer explains to the court

161
00:06:45.345 --> 00:06:46.565
and the next provider of care

162
00:06:46.565 --> 00:06:48.085
that this patient is discharging

163
00:06:48.225 --> 00:06:49.365
and identifies where they'll be

164
00:06:49.365 --> 00:06:50.485
located for their next hearing.

165
00:06:51.285 --> 00:06:53.085
A conditional release explains

166
00:06:53.085 --> 00:06:54.405
to the patient the conditions

167
00:06:54.405 --> 00:06:55.605
on which they're being released.

168
00:06:56.055 --> 00:06:58.685
These are reviewed with a patient, the patient signs,

169
00:06:58.945 --> 00:07:00.805
and then they're sent to the next provider of care.

170
00:07:01.345 --> 00:07:03.925
If within 30 days a patient is not doing well in the

171
00:07:03.925 --> 00:07:05.565
community and is refusing to comply

172
00:07:05.565 --> 00:07:07.485
with mental health treatment, it can be returned

173
00:07:07.485 --> 00:07:10.765
to the hospital or seen in an emergency room under an order

174
00:07:11.085 --> 00:07:13.645
placement into a restricted environment without a hearing.

175
00:07:14.065 --> 00:07:16.325
If they have been in the community for more than 30 days

176
00:07:16.825 --> 00:07:19.765
and an order of placement into a restricted environment is

177
00:07:19.765 --> 00:07:21.965
completed, then the patient can request a hearing.

178
00:07:23.855 --> 00:07:25.245
Civil commitment is designed

179
00:07:25.245 --> 00:07:28.325
to help understanding each step can help ensure

180
00:07:28.325 --> 00:07:30.965
that individuals receive the care they need in a way

181
00:07:30.965 --> 00:07:32.485
that protects their rights and safety.
